									<h2>

							Find the Right Attorney
					</h2>

									<p>Unlike a standard car crash, rideshare accidents involve multiple layers of potential coverage. A key issue is which “period” the rideshare driver was in at the time of the collision: offline, logged into the app waiting for a ride, en route to pick up a passenger, or actively transporting a rider. Different levels of insurance can apply in each stage, including personal auto policies and large commercial policies maintained by the rideshare company.</p><p>AccidentLogic focuses on finding attorneys who know how to identify the correct coverage and pursue claims under the right policies.</p>

